{{Infobox ancient site |name = Borkowo megalithic cemetery |native_name = |alternate_name = |image = Passage Megalithic Grave, Borkowo, Poland.JPG |alt = |caption = Borkowo Passage Grave |map_type = Poland |map_alt = |relief = yes |location = [[Sławno County]] |region = |coordinates = {{coord|54.228700|16.597500|display=inline}} |type = [[Dolmen]] |epochs = [[Chalcolithic Age|Copper Age]] / [[Bronze Age]] }} '''Borkowo megalithic cemetery''' is a prehistoric burial ground situated in the county of [[Sławno County|Sławno]], in [[Western Pomerania]], [[Poland]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Gimbutas|first=Marija|authorlink=Marija Gimbutas|title=Bronze Age Cultures in Central and Eastern Europe|page=391|year=1965|publisher=Mouton & Co.}}</ref>
The site consists of a [[passage grave]], unchambered [[long barrow]]s, and other [[tumuli]].<ref name="backy">{{Cite book|last=Bakker|first=J. A.|title=The Ducht Hunebedden: Megalithic Tombs of the Funnel Beaker Culture|publisher=International Monographs in Prehistory|year=1992|page=74}}</ref> The most impressive monument, Borkowo 1, is passage grave made with heavy boulders and capstones.<ref name="backy"/> It is around 4.5 metres long, with a width of 1.5 metres.<ref name="backy"/> Excavations revealed a cremation and a few pottery sherds.<ref name="backy"/> The grave is assigned to the [[Funnelbeaker culture]] of the [[Chalcolithic Age]].<ref name="backy"/>
